      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 996.2-generation Carrera is a mechanically robust example featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine paired with a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle. The powertrain benefits from a dual-row ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced rear main seal (RMS), ensuring long-term reliability. The chassis retains its signature telepathic feedback thanks to a refreshed multi-link rear suspension and Bilstein B6 dampers. Braking is handled by factory-spec four-piston monobloc calipers with excellent bite and no signs of fade. A clean DME report confirms the engine has been operated within safe RPM parameters. This is a driver-oriented machine with a dry undercarriage and a linear power band that thrives toward the redline.",
